review_blob: Bottle from Trader Joes.  Drunk cold, as American light beers should be.  Drunk out of bottle, so no observations on the head.  Most astonishing thing was lack of any discernable flavor, either good or bad.  Id compare it to Natty Light but without Nattys sweetness on the end.  As far as light beers go, this is inoffensive and decent, and has a cool bottle which might impress your non-beer snob friends.

Drank many of these from a bottle in Managua, Nicaragua.  Victoria is pretty much the national beer in Nicaragua.  Its major competiitor are Tona and Buffalo.  In my opinion, Victoria is the best.  In Nicaragua, this beer is actually more expensive than their rum. Light yellow color, slightly hoppy, little head.  Best of the Central American beers Ive had, as is one of the few that didnt always taste skunked.  Good on a hot day with lime.   

BTW, the picture on this page is wrong.
bottle. deep red color.  Very dry, almost bitter.  black cherry flavor, but not sweet.  almost more like a wine.
draft. deep brown/black.  chocalete hints in flavor.  strong, but drinkable.  foamy head, little lacing.
awesome beer. bottle. deep brown w/ thick head. smooth, assertive flavor.  moderate alcohol finish.
Bottle.  extremely fizzy, good pop from the unccorking.  Nice red color.  Very nice as an after-dinner beer in place of sweets.  Very sweet, slight bitterness/dryness on the back end.

I thoroughly enjoyed this lambic.  Bottle, poured into red wine glass.  Slight head, nice full mouth feel.  light yellow/gold color.  good peach flavor but able to taste a little more than just the fruit. I loved this lambic.
bottle. nice brown color, clear hoppy scent.  Not really what I was expecting... smooth and drinkable but not especially to my liking.
bottle.  slightly cloudy golden color, thin foamy head.  slight fruity smell, weak flavor.  A little better as it warms up.  Not much here; a decent beer but just not enough flavor to it.
excellent beer; this is probably my favorite beer tor drink when Im out on the town or at a barbecue.  Smooth, assertive flavor but not as heavy as youd expect from the coloring.

excellent beer.  black with light caramel-brown foam.  Foam coats sides of glass nicely as drunk.  

Flavor is full, strong hoppy at the back end but not overpowering.  Like a meal.
